display="block">  \begin {aligned}    M_0 &amp;= I^n\\    M_{k+1} &amp;= I^n + {\mathopen {}\left (M\cdot  M_k\right )\mathclose {}}  \end {aligned} </fr:tex><fr:p>Thus we have a recursive algorithm that can deicde whether there is a path between two elemetns in a finite <fr:link
href="jms-00JC.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JC">directed graph</fr:link>: indeed, there is a path from <fr:tex>s</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>t</fr:tex> in <fr:tex>R</fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex>M^*_{s,t} =\mathsf {true}</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
