style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex>M_k</fr:tex>’s</html:span> to get a better understanding.</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block">   \begin {aligned}    M_1 &amp;= I^n + M\cdot  M_0    \\    &amp;= I^n+M\cdot  I^n    \\    &amp;= I^n + M    \\    M_2 &amp;= I^n + M\cdot  M_1    \\    &amp;= I^n + M\cdot  (I^n + M)    \\    &amp;= I^n + M\cdot  I^n + M\cdot  M    \\    &amp;= I^n + M + M^2   \end {aligned}  </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By induction, we can extend the pattern above to a closed form for each <fr:tex>M_k</fr:tex>. In particular, we deduce that <fr:tex>M_k = \sum _{l\leq  k} M^l</fr:tex> by recalling from <fr:ref
addr="jms-00J3"
href="jms-00J3.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> that the <fr:link
href="jms-00IT.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IT">identity matrix</fr:link> is the neutral element for <fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IV">matrix multiplication</fr:link>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex>M_n =\sum _{k \leq  n}M^k</fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Our goal is to show that <fr:tex>M_n = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}} R^{\circ  *}</fr:tex>; we have already seen in <fr:ref
addr="jms-00JR"
href="jms-00JR.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> and <fr:ref
addr="jms-00J2"
href="jms-00J2.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> that <fr:link
href="jms-00JO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JO">matrix addition</fr:link> corresponds to union of <fr:link
href="jms-00I7.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00I7">relations</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IV">matrix multiplication</fr:link> corresponds to <fr:link
href="jms-00IN.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IN">relational composition</fr:link>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>By <fr:ref
addr="jms-00JU"
href="jms-00JU.xml"
taxon="Observation"></fr:ref> (<fr:link
href="jms-00JU.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JU">reflexive-transitive closure of <fr:em>finite</fr:em> <fr:link
href="jms-00JF.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JF">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have <fr:tex>R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}</fr:tex>. Therefore:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block">   \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ *} = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}  </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By <fr:ref
addr="jms-00JR"
href="jms-00JR.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> (<fr:link
href="jms-00JR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JR"><fr:link
href="jms-00JO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JO">matrix addition</fr:link> and union of <fr:link
href="jms-00I7.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00I7">relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block">   \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}   =   \sum _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  </fr:tex>

 By <fr:ref
addr="jms-00J2"
href="jms-00J2.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> (<fr:link
href="jms-00J2.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00J2"><fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IV">matrix product</fr:link> is <fr:link
href="jms-00IN.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IN">relational composition</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:
 <fr:tex
display="block">   \sum _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  =   \sum _{k\leq  n} {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\right )\mathclose {}}^k   =   \sum _{k\leq  n} M^k   = M_n  </fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>